The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Maruti in pact with Bellsonica

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, July 12: Maruti Udyog Ltd has set up a joint venture with Bellsonica Corporation.

 The venture, Bellsonica Auto Component India Pvt Ltd, will be operational from November. Maruti will hold a 30 per cent stake and Bellsonica 70 per cent in the company whose paid-up capital is Rs 12 crore.

 The JV, approved by the Foreign Investment Promotion Board, is being set up by Bellsonica on the recommendations of Suzuki Motor Corporation of Japan. 




